sentences: Kwon Na-ra (Korean: 권나라) (changed her name legally to Kwon Ah-yoon (Korean: 권아윤), known by her stage name Nara, is a South Korean singer and actress.
She is best known as one of the original members of the South Korean girl group Hello Venus.
Career ==
Beginnings and acting debut =
Nara became an acting trainee for Fantagio Entertainment when she was in middle school.
She joined the girl group Hello Venus as a founding member where she went by the stage name "Nara".
They debuted on May 9, 2012 with the mini-album Venus, which contained four tracks.
The single "Venus" reached number 35 on the Gaon chart.
Aside from her group activities, Nara appeared as a cameo role as a stewardess on the 20th episode of the SBS drama Take Care of Us, Captain with fellow Hello Venus member, Yooyoung.
